comments: One of several "Soundie" recordings made by Sister Rosetta Tharpe with Lucky Millinder's Orchestra in 1941. Soundie recordings were short films designed for replaying on a "Panoram" machine, which was a type of juke box that played 16 mm films. This recording was not available on an audio release until the CD era.
